cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses privacy and security issues in messaging systems and proposes a solution to protect user privacy. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the design and implementation of the Zephyr messaging system. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses the decentralized architecture of Zephyr. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of implementing private messaging over internet-related services. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of Zephyr and its software design.
